arch - all of which interrogate the fundamental conceptions of »act« and »actor« that underwrite both popular and academic notions of performance in moving image culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAesthetics. 4aBody. 4aEthics. 4aFilm. 4aMedia Aesthetics. 4aMedia Studies. 4aMoving Image Studies. 4aPerformance Studies. 4aTheatre Studies. 4aTheatre. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aBody.  aEthics.  aFilm.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Studies.  aMoving Image Studies.  aPerformance Studies.  aTheatre Studies.  aTheatre.1 aAdamou, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarker, Jennifer M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaron, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeckman, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDistelmeyer, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoellmer, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlitre, Kathrina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagener, Malte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHovland, Ceri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaine, Tarja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevitt, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevitt, Deborah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMarie, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDonald, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMersch, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat